# scripts/secrets/.secrets.example
#
# This file is a CHECKLIST for operators, NOT a config file.
# The actual values live ONLY in GitHub Environments (not repo-level
# secrets, not variables). Nothing here is sourced or parsed.
#
# ── Where secrets live ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# All secrets live in GH Environments, not repo-level Actions secrets.
# Each environment (dev / test / prod) holds the SAME key names but
# DIFFERENT values:
#
#   Settings → Environments → dev   → Secrets
#   Settings → Environments → test  → Secrets
#   Settings → Environments → prod  → Secrets
#
# fetch_secrets.sh's tier input picks which env's secret store is read.
# This gives you:
#   - Visual grouping (3 separate pages in GH UI)
#   - Independent access control per tier
#   - Required reviewers (typically on 'prod' only) for blast radius
#
# ── To add a new secret in a tier ──────────────────────────────────────────
#   1. Settings → Environments → <tier> → Secrets → "Add secret"
#   2. Name = one of the keys below (UPPER_SNAKE_CASE, no tier suffix)
#   3. Value = the tier-specific value
#   4. (For TENCENT_DB_ADMIN_URL) only put it in env 'prod' — it's a
#      shared superuser DSN, only prod dispatch needs it
#   5. (Optional) Configure Required reviewers on env 'prod' to gate
#      secret changes — strongly recommended
#   6. Verify with:
#        gh workflow run sync-secrets.yml -f tier=<tier> -f which=all -f request_id=verify
#        # (then gh run download to confirm round-trip)
#
# ── Naming convention ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Keys are UNSUFFIXED (AI_API_KEY, not AI_API_KEY_DEV). The Environment
# itself is the namespace. If you put AI_API_KEY in all three envs, the
# job's `environment: ${{ inputs.tier }}` scopes ${{ secrets.AI_API_KEY }}
# to that env's value. Same key name, three values, no collision.
#
# ── CLI usage ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
#   # Dev host (default tier is dev):
#   eval "$(scripts/secrets/fetch_secrets.sh eval-cms)"
#   eval "$(scripts/secrets/fetch_secrets.sh eval-db)"
#
#   # Test host (CI / staging):
#   eval "$(scripts/secrets/fetch_secrets.sh eval-cms:test)"
#   eval "$(scripts/secrets/fetch_secrets.sh eval-db:test)"
#
#   # Prod host (pauses for required reviewers if configured):
#   eval "$(scripts/secrets/fetch_secrets.sh eval-cms:prod)"
#   eval "$(scripts/secrets/fetch_secrets.sh eval-db:prod)"
#   # eval-db:prod ALSO pulls TENCENT_DB_ADMIN_URL (prod-only)

# ---- CMS segment (fetch_secrets.sh eval-cms) ----
#
# AI_API_KEY              sk-...                    # OpenAI-compatible
# AI_BASE_URL             https://api.openai.com/v1 # default
# AI_MODEL                gpt-3.5-turbo             # or gpt-4o / MiniMax-M3 / etc.
#
# TENCENT_SECRET_ID       AKID...                   # Tencent Cloud TTS
# TENCENT_SECRET_KEY      ...
# TENCENT_APP_ID          ...
#
# CLOUD_PROVIDER          tencent_cos               # or "local_fs" for no-cloud
# CLOUD_BUCKET            english-audio-xxx
# CLOUD_REGION            ap-guangzhou
# CLOUD_ACCESS_KEY        ...
# CLOUD_SECRET_KEY        ...
# CLOUD_ENDPOINT          (optional CDN custom domain)

# ---- DB segment (fetch_secrets.sh eval-db) ----
#
# TENCENT_DB_HOST         tencent-pg-xxx.tencentcloud.com:5432
# TENCENT_DB_USER         english_dev_alice         # dev: 派生 from $USER
#                                                  # test/prod: fixed
# TENCENT_DB_PASSWORD     24-char URL-safe          # matches the role password
#
# TENCENT_DB_ADMIN_URL    (only in env 'prod'; 一性 admin DSN)
#                        # 组成字段 (分别存储, 不要拼成完整 DSN 写进任何 git 跟踪文件):
#                        #   user = postgres
#                        #   password = <一次性 admin 密码, 从腾讯云控制台获取>
#                        #   host = <TENCENT_DB_HOST 同值>
#                        #   port = 5432
#                        #   db   = postgres
#                        # 用途: bootstrap_tencent.sh 用它做 CREATE ROLE / DATABASE /
#                        #       GRANT (每个 host 一次), 之后 reset-db / cleanup 不再需要
#                        # ⚠️ 永远不要把完整 DSN 写进任何 git 跟踪文件 — 走 GH Secrets

# Recommended workflow (GH Secrets path — no .secrets/tencent_db_admin_url file
# ever written to disk):
#
#   # 1. Build the three Environments (UI 操作, 一次性):
#   #    Settings → Environments → New environment → 'dev'  (no reviewers)
#   #    Settings → Environments → New environment → 'test' (no reviewers)
#   #    Settings → Environments → New environment → 'prod' (Required reviewers: at least 1)
#
#   # 2. Push per-tier secrets (值的形态见上面 # ---- 段):
#   #    12 dev secrets:
#   for k in AI_API_KEY AI_BASE_URL AI_MODEL TENCENT_SECRET_ID TENCENT_SECRET_KEY \
#            TENCENT_APP_ID CLOUD_PROVIDER CLOUD_BUCKET CLOUD_REGION \
#            CLOUD_ACCESS_KEY CLOUD_SECRET_KEY TENCENT_DB_PASSWORD; do
#     gh secret set "$k" --env dev --body "<dev value>"
#   done
#   #    12 test secrets: same loop with --env test
#   #    13 prod secrets: same loop with --env prod + add TENCENT_DB_ADMIN_URL
#
#   # 3. On every host, every shell session:
#   cd <repo>
#   eval "$(scripts/secrets/fetch_secrets.sh eval-db)"        # dev
#   eval "$(scripts/secrets/fetch_secrets.sh eval-db:test)"   # test
#   eval "$(scripts/secrets/fetch_secrets.sh eval-db:prod)"   # prod (may pause for reviewer)
#   ./ops/<dev|test|prod>/setup.sh bootstrap                  # no file write needed

# Standalone fallback (no GH):
#   If you don't want to use GitHub Secrets at all (e.g. on an isolated
#   network), keep using cms/.env and .secrets/ as before. fetch_secrets.sh
#   is purely additive — its absence doesn't break anything.
